The KRCDPP SMP specifies immediate actions KRCDPP personnel will take during a spill event including:
A? Internal notification procedures;
A? Evacuation procedures;
A? PPE requirements;
A? Spill response and cleanup procedures; 
A? Safe operating procedures for the aqueous ammonia tank and equipment; and
A? Notification procedures to outside agencies.

Planned Changes to Improve Safety
The KRCDPP underwent extensive health and safety review during the CEC licensing process.  No additional safety measures beyond the mitigation measures proposed to the CEC as a condition of certification are planned at this time.
